<item>
            <title>[WICKET-5416] BOM in UTF markup file breaks encoding detection</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-5416</link>
                <project id="12310561" key="WICKET">Wicket</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I have project with internationalization and experienced this problem with one of the pages with non-english content. Page had UTF-8 encoding, but my JVM encoding is different. I always use &quot;&amp;lt;?xml encoding ... ?&amp;gt;&quot; to specify encoding for markup pages (and &quot;MarkupSettings.defaultMarkupEncoding&quot; is not set).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unexpectedly I got problem with bad encoding on page. After several hours of debugging I found what source of this issue was UTF BOM (Byte order mark) at the beggining of file and inability of &quot;XmlReader&quot; to process it. &quot;XmlReader.getXmlDeclaration&quot; tries to match xml declaration with regular expression, but fails because of BOM. After that encoding defaults to JVM encoding.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s possible to use &quot;org.apache.commons.io.input.BOMInputStream&quot; to handle BOM or you could handle it manually inside &quot;XmlReader&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;PS: issue found with Wicket 1.5.10 and I see same code in 6.12.0 without BOM handling, so I added it to &quot;Affects Version/s&quot;, but no proof-in-code available from me at this moment.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Windows 7, jdk1.7.0_45</environment>
